I'll design a reverse-engineered, self-manifesting IDE builder that works backwards from the final feature to the first keystroke—no placeholders, no circular dependencies, actual production code that compiles when its dependencies are ready.
The Reverse-Engineered Manifestation Plan
Working backwards from the "last" feature to the "first" application entry point. Each layer manifests only what it needs from the layer above, creating concrete code that wires itself into existence.
Phase Ω: The Final Feature (The "Last" Thing)
